I've been watching abridged since day 1. I actually started with Lanipator's Yu Yu Hakusho abridged. Loved it, subscribed instantly. The way DBA goofed all of the little things by almost taking thoughts from my mind as if there was a consensus this whole time about certain things in the show that I never knew. It's always giving me great nostalgia, the comfort of knowing that it's not just me in so many things. The lovable portrayals of the characters.

You guys are awesome. All of you. Thank you for all of the blood and sweat you guys put into this. You guys have given so much joy and laughter with this gem and I can't thank you enough.

I hope when you guys are older, you bring it back in a unanimous mid-life crisis. Until then, best of luck to you all, never unsubscribing, always supporting this channel.

Just curious, but have you considered doing short clips in DBZA format? Not a continuation of the story at all, but if you think of a joke for one small scene that you think would work and just make that? I think it would be easier on you all, being able to just do a short if you think of one, without people expecting a new episode every week, and only making it if the joke's there. Honestly, I don't know if that would make you run into the same copyright issues as before. But just as an example though, ever since the scene in Super came out with the Universe 6 Namekians fusing into 2 beings, all I could think about was how you all could handle that considering what you did with Piccollo, Nail, and Kami.

Anyways, just something I thought you might consider, and thank you again for all your hard work!

I don't know if anyone will read this, but after everything DBZA and TFS brought me, I feel I have to say something. Me and my friends used to get together and watch each new episode of DBZA. I've catches every episode of FF7.

I'm sorry to see it go, but I have no right to demand anything. So maybe DBZA is over. Maybe FF7 is coming to an end. I love these shows. My friends love these shows. We sit around playing games on Skype almost every night an quote this show at each other. But as a creative type, I know how it feels to realize the dread setting in that you've stopped enjoying the creative process.

I'll miss this show. It will always hold a place in my heart, and as one of my favorite shows ever, even over actual shows. This past Christmas, I literally went back and watched the DBZA Christmas movie. But even after it ends, after the dust settles, what you guys have provided for us is more than anyone could've asked for.

In my eyes, you guys will always be legendary, and I look forward to watching whatever it is that you guys produce. Remember that your fans always have your backs, and thank you for all the years of entertainment you guys provided. Sincerely, Thank you.

-A fan
